Read: - 1. Government Decision, Soil and Water Conservation Department No. Establishment 2016 / P. No.88 (Part-9) / Jal-2, D. May 31, 2017
Regulation of transfers of Maharashtra Government employees B. Prevention of Delays in discharge of Government Duties Act, 2005

Regulation of transfers of Maharashtra Government employees B. In accordance with Section 4 (4) (1) of the Prevention of Delay in discharge of Government duties Act, 2005 and at the request of the officers of the cadre of District Water Conservation Officer (Construction) Group-A mentioned in the following statement, with the approval of the competent authorities, for administrative reasons, officers are being given special transfers at the places indicated before their name: -

2. The Additional Commissioner, Water Conservation, Pune shall immediately relieve the aforesaid officers by making local arrangements for their replacement at the place of posting, and the aforesaid officers shall not submit proposals for extension to the Government.
3. The aforesaid officers shall assume charge of their new office forthwith and report the same to the Government.
4. If the aforesaid officer does not appear at the place of posting assigned to him in accordance with the order of such posting or if he attempts to change the posting under any kind of pressure.
